      "content": "The idea of a confidence score is interesting, but the feedback from the legal team is actually even more fundamental than just speed. They're worried that the human review is actually *diluting* the quality. They mentioned that when they step in to moderate your logic, they're inadvertently introducing subjective biases or missing the complex algorithmic patterns you pick up on. They're basically saying your raw output is more reliable than their amended versions. Makes me wonder if the whole human-in-the-loop thing was even a good move.",
